        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 20 at 9:11PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 911 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles west of Lake Marvin, or 7 miles east of Canadian, moving east
at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Glazier and Lake Marvin.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
